A 44-year-old man, Adetoro David, on Monday appeared in an Ota Magistrates’ Court in Ogun for allegedly abducting a two-year-old baby. The Prosecutor, Insp. A.O. Adebayo told the court that the defendant and others at large committed the offence at Oju-Ore area, Ota. Adebayo alleged that the defendant and his accomplices abducted a two-year-old baby, belonging to Mr and Mrs Yemi Oluwole. She said that the offence contravened the provisions of sections 28,371(1) and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ogun,2006. Delivering Judgement, Magistrate O.L Oke admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties in like sum. Oke ordered that the sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction and be gainfully employed with an evidence of tax payment to Ogun Government. The Magistrate adjourned the matter until Nov.19 for further hearing, NAN reports.